Privacy Policy for Library Management System

Last Updated: [7-12-2025]

1. Information We Collect
We collect the following personal information when you register for our library services:
- Student's full name
- Learning Reference Number (LRN)
- Contact number
- Parent/Guardian's name
- Parent/Guardian's contact number
- Facebook account name
- School-related information

2. How We Use Your Information
The collected information is used for:
- Managing book borrowing records
- Contacting students or parents regarding overdue books
- Verifying student identity during transactions
- Emergency contact purposes
- Library-related communications

3. Information Protection
We are committed to protecting your personal information by:
- Restricting access to authorized personnel only
- Maintaining secure digital storage systems
- Not sharing information with third parties
- Regular system security updates

4. Data Retention
- We retain your information while you are an active library user
- Records are maintained according to school policy requirements
- You may request data deletion after graduating/leaving the school

5. Your Rights
You have the right to:
- Access your personal information
- Request corrections to your data
- Know how your information is being used
- Request data deletion (subject to school policy)

6. Contact Us
For questions about this privacy policy or your personal information, please contact:
[School Library Name]
[Contact Information]
[Email Address]

Note: This privacy policy may be updated periodically to reflect any changes in our data handling practices.